 and Wendy Brown to examine the side effects that can be generated when queers assimilate, and argues for a reinvigorated queer essentialism in order to claim a separate and visible political and activist space within U.S. culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aGay and lesbian studieszUnited States. 0aGay peoplezUnited StatesxSocial conditions. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Lesbian / Gay Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Gay Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143842767640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438427676423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438427676/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles